# GX-BX8B-SPIKE-R1
# Pinned inputs for the Java browser toolchain (Bx-8b). See docs/browser-runtimes.md
# and the Bx-8b entry in docs/ROADMAP.md.
#
# THIS FILE IS PART OF THE CACHE KEY once it reaches main: pages.yml/ci.yml hash
# tools/**, so editing any pin here invalidates the vendor cache and forces a
# rebuild. One place to bump, no manual key juggling. Same shape as
# tools/dart-toolchain/pins.env and tools/arm64-toolchain/pins.env.

# THE SOURCE. konsoletyper/teavm-javac -- "Java compiler in the browser", which
# is what serves https://teavm.org/playground/compiler.wasm.
#
# NOT konsoletyper/teavm. That is the AOT compiler; its releases (0.15.0 etc)
# are Maven artifacts and contain no compiler.wasm at all. Two different
# projects by the same author, and picking the wrong one wastes the round. TeaVM
# 0.13's own release notes say the browser-compiler work "was done mostly
# outside TeaVM".
TEAVM_JAVAC_REPO=https://github.com/konsoletyper/teavm-javac.git

# WHY A SHA AND NOT A VERSION. teavm-javac publishes NO releases and NO tags.
# Its README does not name a version; it says "The latest WebAssembly module can
# be found here" and points at the maintainer's own web server. So there is no
# upstream version to pin to, and a commit SHA is the only pin that exists.
#
# BLANK ON PURPOSE FOR ROUND 1. The spike resolves master HEAD, prints it, and
# shouts UNPINNED. Round 2 pastes the SHA in here and the build becomes
# reproducible. Once this is real work rather than a spike, build-teavm-javac.sh
# must REFUSE on a blank -- the way build-dart2js.sh refuses when the installed
# dart does not match DART_SDK_VERSION. A pin that is only a comment is not a pin.
TEAVM_JAVAC_COMMIT=

# The README states "You need Java 21 installed on your machine." Not the 25 that
# ci.yml's setup-java uses for the CLI Java track -- this is the toolchain's own
# requirement, and a spike that quietly builds on a different JDK is testing
# something other than what it will ship.
TEAVM_JAVAC_JDK=21

# Left empty until the recon says what the build actually offers. The README
# claims:  ./gradlew :compiler:build  ->  compiler/build/distributions/dist.zip
# It also says the two classlib archives are "generated with special tool",
# which is named nowhere. Round 1 finds the tool by reading the build, not by
# guessing at it.
TEAVM_JAVAC_BUILD_TASK=
